        "text": "<@UJBAJNFLK>'s link <https:\/\/feelingofcomputing.slack.com\/archives\/C5U3SEW6A\/p1776099082547179> spawned this thought, among others, as I watched:\n\n&gt; **TL;DR** — Old code is dying. The code isn't the problem. The business rules embedded in it are. LLMs can extract those rules into a factbase. A factbase can be rewritten into any target language. This is Design Recovery, and it is the right job for LLMs.\n<https:\/\/open.substack.com\/pub\/programmingsimplicity\/p\/llms-as-design-recovery-engines?r=1egdky&amp;utm_campaign=post&amp;utm_medium=web&amp;showWelcomeOnShare=true|LLMs as Design Recovery Engines>",
